        <h2 class="left-heading destination-section-heading">Angers, France</h2>
        <p>The first castle you'll encounter on your route is the 9th century <strong>Chateau d'Angers</strong>, a well-preserved castle surrounded by imposing medieval walls and a former moat. This castle has a long history of use by important figures throughout history and was greatly expanded in the 13th century.</p>
        <!-- Read More Read Less Tab -->
        <div class="hidden-content">
            <h3>Apocalypse Tapestry</h3>
            <p>The castle now serves as the world's largest medieval tapestry museum, which hosts the massive 14th century <strong>Apocalypse Tapestry</strong>, a French national treasure.</p>
            <p>Also in Angers you might like to visit the <strong>Adam House</strong> (also known as the House of Artisans), a charming half-timbered medieval structure which houses some very interesting and unique souvenirs.</p>
        </div>
