        <p>Much further east along the Loire River from Angers is the city of Saumur, where you'll find the remarkable 10th century <strong>Chateau de Saumur</strong>. This castle is best admired briefly from the outside, as the castle's interior is quite underwhelming.</p>
        <p>Continue east along the valley to the fairytale-like 17th century <strong>Chateau d'Usse</strong>, which was literally the inspiration for the Sleeping Beauty castle in the original fairy tale by famous author Charles Perrault.</p>
    </section>




