        <h2 class="left-heading destination-section-heading">Tours, France</h2>
        <p>A bit futher east of the Chateau d'Usse near the city of Tours is the <strong>Chateau de Langeais</strong>, a majestic 15th century castle with historic furnishings. Nearby is the 14th century <strong>Chateau de Villandry</strong> with its beautiful massive formal gardens you can explore. This castle's gardens are extremely well-manicured and quite photogenic.</p>
        <!-- Read More Read Less Tab -->
        <div class="hidden-content">
            <h3>Tours, France</h3>
            <p>Continue to the large city of Tours, which sits on the Loire River. Here you can admire the towering <strong>Saint-Gatien Cathedral</strong> and its elaborate gothic architecture. If you'd like to see some charming half-timbered medieval homes, you can head over the the city's <strong>Place Plumereau</strong> square, which also hosts many great cafes and restaurants.</p>
        </div>
