    <section class="destination-section">
        <a class="anchor" id="orleans"></a>
        <h2 class="left-heading destination-section-heading">Orleans, France</h2>
        <p>Just west of the city of Orleans is an impressive minor castle, the 12th century <strong>Chateau de Meung-sur-Loire</strong>. This imposing medieval castle contains fine historic interiors which you can see via tour.</p>
        <p>The top sight within the city of Orleans is the medieval <strong>Sainte-Croix Cathedral</strong>. This cathedral is famous for its association with Joan of Arc, who is now features in the church's stain glass windows. The cathedral is gigantic and showcases complex gothic architecture.</p>
        <!-- Read More Read Less Tab -->
        <div class="hidden-content">
            <p>Adjacent to the cathedral is the <strong>Hotel Groslot</strong>, a lovely medieval building with ornate era-appropriate furnishings.</p>
            <h3>Chateau de Sully-sur-Loire</h3>
            <p>Beyond Orleans is one more castle you might like to visit, the brilliant medieval <strong>Chateau de Sully-sur-Loire</strong>, which is completely surrounded by a moat. This enchanting castle contains historic furnishings and is quite picturesque.</p>
